Virtual private services with tsnet
使用 tsnet 的虛擬專用服務

Tailscale lets you connect to your computers from anywhere in the world. We call this setup a virtual private network. Any device on the tailnet (our term for a Tailscale network) can connect directly to any other device on the tailnet. When you do this you can access your NAS from anywhere, RDP (Remote Desktop Protocol) into your gaming PC in Canada to check messages from the Canadian tax authority, or even SSH into production with Tailscale SSH. Everything will just work.
Tailscale 允許您從世界任何地方連接到您的電腦。我們將此設置稱為虛擬專用網路。尾網（我們對 Tailscale 網路的術語）上的任何設備都可以直接連接到尾網上的任何其他設備。當您這樣做時，您可以從任何地方訪問您的 NAS，將 RDP（遠端桌面協定）連接到您在加拿大的遊戲 PC 中以檢查來自加拿大稅務機關的消息，甚至可以使用 Tailscale SSH 通過SSH連接到生產環境。一切都會順利進行。

This isn’t limited to your computers, phones, and servers, though. You can use Tailscale as a library in Go programs to allow them to connect to your tailnet as though it were a separate computer. You can also use Tailscale to run multiple services with different confidentiality levels on the same machine. This will allow you to separate support tooling from data analytics without having to run them on multiple servers or virtual machines. The only way that the tools could be exposed is over Tailscale — meaning that there’s no way to get into them from outside your tailnet.
不過，這不僅限於您的計算機、電話和伺服器。您可以將 Tailscale 用作 Go 程式中的庫，以允許它們連接到您的 tailnet，就像它是一台單獨的電腦一樣。您還可以使用 Tailscale 在同一台電腦上運行具有不同機密性的多個服務。這將允許您將支援工具與數據分析分開，而無需在多個伺服器或虛擬機上運行它們。這些工具暴露的唯一方式是通過Tailscale——這意味著無法從你的tailnet之外進入它們。

Today I’m going to explain more about how you can use tsnet to make your internal services easier to run, access, and secure by transforming them into virtual private services on your tailnet. By the end of this post you should have an understanding of what virtual private services are, how they benefit you, and how to write one using Tailscale as a library. Finally, I will give you some ideas for how you could take this one step further.
今天，我將詳細解釋如何使用 tsnet 將內部服務轉換為尾網上的虛擬專用服務，從而使內部服務更易於運行、訪問和保護。在這篇文章的最後，您應該瞭解什麼是虛擬專用服務，它們如何使您受益，以及如何使用Tailscale作為庫編寫虛擬專用服務。最後，我將為您提供一些關於如何更進一步的想法。

Virtual private services  虛擬專用服務

When you add a laptop or phone to your tailnet, Tailscale assigns it its own IP address and DNS name. This allows you to connect over Tailscale’s encrypted tunnel so you can access your NAS from the coffee shop to grab whatever files you need. This also allows you to request an HTTPS certificate from Let’s Encrypt so you can run whatever services you want over HTTPS.
當您將筆記型電腦或手機加入到尾網時，Tailscale 會為其分配自己的IP位址和 DNS 名稱。這允許通過 Tailscale 的加密隧道進行連接，以便您可以從咖啡店訪問您的 NAS 以獲取您需要的任何檔。這也允許您從 Let's Encrypt 請求 HTTPS 證書，以便您可以通過 HTTPS 執行您想要的任何服務。

However, this only lets you get one DNS name and IP address per system. Currently, running multiple services with separate domain names on the same system is impossible with Tailscale, but there is a workaround. Using tsnet, you can embed Tailscale as a library in an existing Go program. tsnet takes all of the goodness of Tailscale and lets you access it all from userspace instead of having to wade through the nightmare of configuring multiple VPN connections on the same machines.
但是，這隻允許您為每個系統獲取一個 DNS 名稱和 IP 位址。 目前，在同一 系統是不可能的，但有一種解決方法。用 tsnet 中，您可以將 Tailscale 作為庫嵌入到現有 Go 程式中。tsnet 利用了Tailscale的所有優點，並允許您從用戶空間訪問它，而不必費力地經歷在同一台電腦上組態多個 VPN 連接的噩夢。

When you start a virtual private service with tsnet, your Go program will get its own IP address, DNS name, and the ability to grab its own HTTPS certificate. You can ping the service instead of the server it’s on. You can listen on privileged ports like the HTTP and HTTPS ports without having to run your service as root. You can use ACL tags and groups to separate out access to that service individually. Finally, you can run multiple of these services on the same machine without having to have root permissions or do anything beyond running the programs on the machines. You don’t even need to expose them anywhere else besides over Tailscale. All of this happens in the same OS process: All the magic of Tailscale becomes a library like any other, allowing you to create virtual private services for your team.
當您使用 tsnet 啟動虛擬專用服務時，您的 Go 程式將獲得自己的 IP 位址、DNS 名稱以及獲取自己的 HTTPS 證書的能力。您可以 ping 服務，而不是它所在的伺服器。您可以偵聽 HTTP 和 HTTPS 連接埠等特權埠，而無需以 root 身份運行您的服務。您可以使用 ACL 標籤和組單獨分離對該服務的訪問。最後，您可以在同一台計算機上運行多個這些服務，而無需root許可權，也無需執行除在電腦上運行程式之外的任何作。您甚至不需要在 Tailscale 以外的任何其他位置公開它們。所有這些都發生在同一個作系統進程中：Tailscale 的所有魔力都變成了一個像任何其他庫一樣的庫，允許您為您的團隊創建虛擬專用服務。

How to make your own hello server
如何製作自己的 hello 伺服器

I’m going to show you how to create a minimal “hello” service that will let any connecting user know who Tailscale thinks they are. To start, install the latest version of the Go programming language and restart your terminal program. Next, create a folder for the code with a command such as this:
我將向您展示如何創建一個最小的 「hello」 服務，讓任何連接使用者都知道 Tailscale 認為他們是誰。首先，安裝最新版本的 Go 程式設計語言並重新啟動您的終端程式。接下來，使用如下命令為代碼創建一個資料夾：

mkdir -p ~/code/whoami
cd ~/code/whoami

Then create a new Go project with this command:
然後使用以下命令建立新的 Go 專案：

go mod init github.com/your-username/whoami

Install tsnet with this command:
使用以下命令安裝 tsnet：

go get tailscale.com/tsnet

Then make a main.go file with the following in it:
然後製作一個 main.go 檔，其中包含以下內容：


package main

import (
	"flag"
	"fmt"
	"html"
	"log"
	"net/http"
	"strings"

	"tailscale.com/tsnet"
)

var (
	hostname = flag.String("hostname", "hello", "hostname for the tailnet")
)

func main() {
	flag.Parse()

	s := &tsnet.Server{
		Hostname: *hostname,
	}

	defer s.Close()

	ln, err := s.Listen("tcp", ":80")
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	defer ln.Close()

	lc, err := s.LocalClient()
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	log.Fatal(http.Serve(ln, http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
		who, err := lc.WhoIs(r.Context(), r.RemoteAddr)
		if err != nil {
			http.Error(w, err.Error(), 500)
			return
		}

		fmt.Fprintf(w, "<html><body><h1>Hello, world!</h1>\n")
		fmt.Fprintf(w, "<p>You are <b>%s</b> from <b>%s</b> (%s)</p>",
			html.EscapeString(who.UserProfile.LoginName),
			html.EscapeString(firstLabel(who.Node.ComputedName)),
			r.RemoteAddr)
	})))
}

func firstLabel(s string) string {
	if hostname, _, ok := strings.Cut(s, "."); ok {
		return hostname
	}

	return s
}

Then generate a new auth key in the admin panel and set it as TS_AUTHKEY= in your environment:
然後在管理面板中生成一個新的身份驗證金鑰並將其設置為 TS_AUTHKEY= 在您的環境中：

export TS_AUTHKEY=tskey-auth-hunter2-hunter2hunter2hunter2

Then you can run it:
然後你可以運行它：

go run .

Once it shows up in your tailnet, you can open http://hello and you’ll get back a simple page that tells you who you are on Tailscale:
一旦它出現在您的尾網中，您就可以打開 http://hello，您將獲得一個簡單的頁面，告訴您您在 Tailscale 上是誰：

You can use this as the basis for other services, too. Replace the http.HandlerFunc with a http.ServeMux and you can host an internal-facing service.
您也可以將其用作其他服務的基礎。將 HTTP 的HandlerFunc 替換為 HTTP.ServeMux，您可以託管面向內部的服務。

Other examples  其他示例

If you need inspiration, here are some ways that we’ve used tsnet for ourselves here at Tailscale.
如果您需要靈感，以下是我們在 Tailscale 為自己使用 tsnet 的一些方法。

One of our first deployments of tsnet was aimed at helping our support team get context for incoming tickets. The support UI we used wasn’t good at giving us information about users, and the process of having to manually look up everything we needed to know was time-consuming and tedious.
我們最早部署 tsnet 的其中一項是幫助我們的支援團隊獲取傳入工單的上下文。我們使用的支援UI不擅長為我們提供有關使用者的資訊，並且必須手動尋找我們需要瞭解的所有內容的過程既耗時又乏味。

We wanted to get the support team more information so they could do their job, but we also didn’t want to open that tool up to the public internet (and risk catastrophic data breaches). We used tsnet to create a service named DAB (Data About Business) that would work with our support tooling so that when support opened a ticket, they got all the information they needed from our control plane at a glance. DAB has been one of our most reliable services inside Tailscale, and it’s hosted on a single AWS instance. HTTPS was seamless with Let’s Encrypt. DAB has easily been the most successful internal project I have ever worked on.
我們想讓支援團隊獲得更多資訊，以便他們能夠完成他們的工作，但我們也不想將該工具開放給公共互聯網（並冒著災難性數據洩露的風險）。我們使用 tsnet 創建了一個名為 DAB（Data About Business）的服務，該服務將與我們的支援工具配合使用，這樣當支援人員打開工單時，他們可以一目瞭然地從我們的控制平面獲得所需的所有資訊。DAB 一直是我們在 Tailscale 中最可靠的服務之一，它託管在單個 AWS 實例上。HTTPS 與 Let's Encrypt 無縫連接。DAB 很容易成為我參與過的最成功的內部專案。

Creating new services is cool, but what’s even cooler is that you can use tsnet to help bridge the gap between Tailscale’s account model and the account model of internal tools like Grafana. We use a tool called proxy-to-grafana inside Tailscale to let us browse and even edit Grafana dashboards without having to have separate Grafana accounts or manage access permissions. We just visit http://mon, and we can do whatever we want.
創建新服務很酷，但更酷的是，您可以使用 tsnet 幫助彌合 Tailscale 的帳戶模型與帳戶之間的差距 Grafana 等內部工具的模型。我們使用一個名為 Tailscale 中的 proxy-to-grafana 讓我們無需擁有 即可流覽甚至編輯 Grafana 儀錶板 單獨的 Grafana 帳戶或管理訪問許可權。我們只是訪問 http://mon，我們可以做任何我們想做的事。

This isn’t limited to web services like Grafana. You can even use tsnet to authenticate to Minecraft, or as a proxy for Postgres to lock down access to your sensitive databases.
這不僅限於 Grafana 等 Web 服務。您甚至可以使用 tsnet 對 Minecraft 進行身份驗證，或作為 Postgres 的代理來鎖定對敏感資料庫的訪問。

We’ve heard about people using tsnet to expose Prometheus metrics and REPL access exclusively over Tailscale. This has allowed those operators to be able to poke inside services in production without having to worry about making custom authentication logic, deal with OAuth2 proxies or other setups to glue it into their identity providers. Access is controlled via Tailscale ACLs.
我們聽說有人使用 tsnet 專門通過 Tailscale 公開 Prometheus 指標和 REPL 訪問。這使得這些作員能夠在生產中探入服務內部，而不必擔心製作 自定義身份驗證邏輯，處理 OAuth2 代理或其他設置以粘附它 到其身份供應商中。通過 Tailscale 控制訪問 ACL 的 ACL 中。

What else could you do with this? How do you use tsnet in your tailnet? We’d love to hear more! Mention us on Twitter @Tailscale or post on /r/tailscale on Reddit.
您還能用它做什麼呢？你如何在尾網中使用 tsnet？我們會 喜歡聽到更多！在 Twitter 上提及我們 @Tailscale或在 Reddit 上的 /r/tailscale 上發帖。
